BACKGROUND

I have held an account with NatWest since I was a child. The Brixton Road branch
is adjacent to my home address. On Tuesday 21 September 2021 at approximately
08:59 UTC, I attended the branch to withdraw cash from my own account using my
passport as identification. I was refused service by the branch manager. I left
the premises. After I had left, NatWest staff called 999. Metropolitan Police
officers attended my home address within approximately five minutes.

I have video evidence of the interaction inside the branch, recorded before I
left.

Full background, video evidence, transcript, and stills are published at:
https://github.com/kingarrrt/natwest


